title: Tsogt-Ochiryn Namuuntsetseg
text:
Tsogt-Ochiryn Namuuntsetseg (; born 31 March 1996) is a <a href="Mongolia">Mongolian</a> freestyle wrestler. 
She competed at the <a href="2019%20World%20Wrestling%20Championships%20%E2%80%93%20Women%27s%20freestyle%2050%20kg">2019 World Wrestling Championships</a>, and 2021 Asian Wrestling Olympic Qualification Tournament.
In 2020, she qualified for the <a href="2020%20Summer%20Olympics">2020 Summer Olympics</a> in Tokyo, Japan. She competed in the <a href="Wrestling%20at%20the%202020%20Summer%20Olympics%20%E2%80%93%20Women%27s%20freestyle%2050%20kg">women's 50 kg</a> event.
